2
00:00:01,297 --> 00:00:04,429
Eunice K. Shriver:
Tonight, in this great stadium,

3
00:00:04,429 --> 00:00:06,627
a new legend is born.

4
00:00:06,627 --> 00:00:12,231
You, athletes,
are the heroes of that legend.

5
00:00:12,231 --> 00:00:15,231
You have taught us
that what truly counts

6
00:00:15,231 --> 00:00:19,165
is the courageous spirit
and the generous heart.

7
00:00:19,165 --> 00:00:22,330
The right to play
on any playing field?

8
00:00:22,330 --> 00:00:23,528
You have earned it.

9
00:00:23,528 --> 00:00:26,132
The right to study
in any school?

10
00:00:26,132 --> 00:00:27,231
You have earned it.

11
00:00:27,231 --> 00:00:28,528
The right to hold a job?

12
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:30,132
You have earned it.

13
00:00:30,132 --> 00:00:33,132
The right to be
anyone's neighbor?

14
00:00:33,132 --> 00:00:34,726
You have earned it.

15
00:00:34,726 --> 00:00:36,330
[ Cheers and applause ]

16
00:00:36,330 --> 00:00:40,726
The days of separation
and segregation are over.

17
00:00:40,726 --> 00:00:43,396
As the philosopher wrote,

18
00:00:43,396 --> 00:00:48,495
"After conquering the winds and
the waves, tides and gravity,

19
00:00:48,495 --> 00:00:51,396
we shall harness
energies of love,

20
00:00:51,396 --> 00:00:55,363
and then, for the second time
in the history of the world,

21
00:00:55,363 --> 00:00:57,561
man will discover fire."

22
00:00:57,561 --> 00:00:59,132
♪♪

